nt": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2068931169782030376", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2068931169782030376", "text": "The Iranian delegation is sounding upbeat, saying that “oil and petrochem exports are waived.” U.S. Treasury / OFAC hasn’t yet published any new guidance. Iran has been exporting lots of crude in recent days, and it’s loading oil tankers again at Kharg Island.", "time": "05:36", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 61114, "likes": 281, "replies": 9, "retweets": 53, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 26, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2068962257317298683", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2068962257317298683", "text": "China's oil imports keep falling and falling in June, below the 10-year low set in May.\n\nAccording to @Vortexa, June 1-20 imports of crude and condy are at 5.3m b/d, down&gt;50% from pre-war levels. \n\nI don't see this as sustainable and a recovery looms (helped by Iranian barrels).", "time": "07:40", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 109327, "likes": 423, "replies": 21, "retweets": 75, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 56, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["China demand", "Demand outlook", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2068970341972758956", "url": "https://x.com/antonisbabo/status/2068970341972758956", "text": "#oott outfit of the ton ㅋㅋ https://t.co/yzOnoSHcyT", "time": "08:12", "author": "antonisbabo", "author_name": "바보", "followers": 39618, "views": 26756, "likes": 1073, "replies": 0, "retweets": 315, "quotes": 40, "bookmarks": 89, "labels": {"relevant": false, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2068972837436629485", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2068972837436629485", "text": "COLUMN: The European Union is buying today &gt;60% of its LNG from the US. \n\nThe massive reliance is prompting a vital question with energy, economic and diplomatic consequences for the European Union: When does a lot become too much?\n\n@Opinion \n\nhttps://t.co/iuZ3LRY0tq", "time": "08:22", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 31981, "likes": 200, "replies": 12, "retweets": 53, "quotes": 7, "bookmarks": 26, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Natural gas"]}}, {"id": "2068975624366989767", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2068975624366989767", "text": "Confirmed crossings through the monitored Strait of Hormuz zone rose sharply over 19–21 June, with 71 total transits recorded. @Kpler #OOTT", "time": "08:33", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 79744, "likes": 300, "replies": 18, "retweets": 73, "quotes": 13, "bookmarks": 31, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069018071755325462", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069018071755325462", "text": "JD Vance before departing from Switzerland:\n\nYesterday was a good day of talks\nStrait of Hormuz is open\nIran/US/mediators set up a mechanism for keeping SoH open\nIran has agreed to invite back nuclear inspectors", "time": "11:22", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 71730, "likes": 251, "replies": 16, "retweets": 34, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 18, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Iran", "Geopolitics", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2069054913078874114", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069054913078874114", "text": "BREAKING: US Treasury issues a general license waiving key Iran oil sanctions until August 21, 2026. On a quick read, it’s a rather wide ranging license, covering exports, shipping and ancillary services, and includes crude, refined products and petrochemicals. https://t.co/N4ayfQzg4C", "time": "13:48", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 104689, "likes": 493, "replies": 25, "retweets": 210, "quotes": 25, "bookmarks": 82, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069062915454324884", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069062915454324884", "text": "Crucially, the general license not only allows importers of Iranian oil to pay Tehran (including via previously sanctioned entities), **but also do so in U.S. dollars!**\n\nFor 60 days at least, Washington is allowing Tehran back in the dollar club to repatriate its petrodollars.", "time": "14:20", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 26731, "likes": 166, "replies": 11, "retweets": 45, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 16, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069065870865838151", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069065870865838151", "text": "It may only last 60 days (I doubt it; likely would become permanent), but the US Treasury’s waiver is effectively rolling back 40-year plus of American oil sanctions against Iran. \n\nEven US refiners are allowed to import Iranian oil and pay for it in greenback!!! https://t.co/nG7xDt1Fwj", "time": "14:31", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 996960, "likes": 3565, "replies": 186, "retweets": 1219, "quotes": 203, "bookmarks": 510, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran"]}}, {"id": "2069087057020903874", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069087057020903874", "text": "🚢Lots of oil leaving Strait of Hormuz (dark and visible)\n🛢️Plus SoH bypass pipelines still going full throttle \n⛽️US / Japan / Europe SPR barrels still flowing \n🇮🇷  Iranian oil now legal for (at least) next 60 days\n🇨🇳China remains on an oil buying strike", "time": "15:56", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 103075, "likes": 654, "replies": 41, "retweets": 128, "quotes": 11, "bookmarks": 79, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Iran", "China demand"]}}, {"id": "2069093369880486277", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2069093369880486277", "text": "US SPR crude inventories fell by ~9.1mb w/w to a multi year low of 331.2mb last week #oott     \nSour down ~3.7mb to 208.2mb   \nSweet down ~5.3mb to 123.0mb https://t.co/hf21qeKrrK", "time": "16:21", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 116688, "likes": 127, "replies": 9, "retweets": 30, "quotes": 13, "bookmarks": 18, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories", "Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2069114299474207035", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069114299474207035", "text": "US put ~9.1 million barrels of SPR oil into the market last week, the 2nd largest weekly release ever (equal to ~1.3 million b/d). Over the last 8 weeks, the US has been releasing &gt;1m b/d on average.", "time": "17:44", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 81719, "likes": 379, "replies": 25, "retweets": 61, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 31, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Supply outlook"]}}, {"id": "2069118892161507539", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2069118892161507539", "text": "I see little chance (probably zero) of a US refiner buying Iranian oil over next 60 days. So why did the White House made such an emphatic move to waive sanctions on US purchases of Iranian oil?\n\na) Gesture to Tehran with little consequence?\nb) Painful Iranian imposition?", "time": "18:02", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 63573, "likes": 239, "replies": 29, "retweets": 41, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 34, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Iran"]}}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 26, "views": 356940, "likes": 613}, {"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 13, "views": 1722309, "likes": 6858}, {"username": "ZmansEnrgyBrain", "name": "Z4 Energy Research", "followers": 11920, "tweets": 8, "views": 28653, "likes": 86}, {"username": "LiveSquawk", "name": "LiveSquawk", "followers": 436346, "tweets": 4, "views": 66876, "likes": 43}, {"username": "Energy_Tidbits", "name": "Dan Tsubouchi", "followers": 15856, "tweets": 3, "views": 9897, "likes": 18}], "top_authors_by_views": [{"username": "JavierBlas", "name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "tweets": 13, "views": 1722309, "likes": 6858}, {"username": "staunovo", "name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "tweets": 26, "views": 356940, "likes": 613}, {"username": "Amena__Bakr", "name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "tweets": 2, "views": 94856, "likes": 358}, {"username": "LiveSquawk", "name": "LiveSquawk", "followers": 436346, "tweets": 4, "views": 66876, "likes": 43}, {"username": "Amalteya3000", "name": "Amalteya", "followers": 773, "tweets": 3, "views": 32004, "likes": 160}], "sentiment": {"price": {"labeled": 93, "relevant": 91, "pos": 27, "neg": 33, "neu": 31, "index": -6.6, "index_weighted": -60.3, "opinion_share": 65.9, "hourly": [{"hour": 0, "pos": 0, "neg": 0, "neu": 1}, {"hour": 1,